==English==
[[File:Britannica Macropaedia.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Volumes 21–24 of ''Britannica'''s ''[[w:Macropædia|Macropædia]]'' (covering topics from ''India'' to ''Norway'') in the [[w:Deutsches Museum|Deutsches Museum]]'s library.]]

[[File:Göttingen-SUB-Encyclopedia.Americana.JPG|thumb|right|250px|Volumes 5–12 of the ''Encyclopedia Americana'' (covering topics from ''Bulgaria'' to ''Goethals'') in the SUB Library at the University of Göttingen, Germany.]]

===Alternative forms===
* {{alt|en|encyclopaedia||Commonwealth}}
* {{alt|en|encyclopædia||dated}}

===Etymology===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*peh₂w-}}
{{etymon|en|id=reference work|:bor|NL.:encyclopaedīa<id:encyclopedia>|tree=1}}
{{bor+|en|NL.|encyclopēdīa, [[encyclopaedia|encyclopaedīa]]|t=general education}}, a [[univerbation|univerbated]] form of {{der|en|grc-koi|ἐγκύκλιος παιδείᾱ|t=education in the circle of arts and sciences}}, from {{der|en|grc|ἐγκύκλιος||[[circular]]}} + {{m|grc|παιδείᾱ||[[childrearing]]; [[education]]}} ([[q.v.]]). Nearly all modern English usage of the word was influenced by the scope and format of the {{der|en|fr|-}} ''{{w|Encyclopédie}}'' by  {{w|Diderot}} [[et al.]] (see quotation).

